Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.10,0:02:50.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He was popular among his friends\Nand called not by his real name,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:52.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but by his nickname "Shige."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:52.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&}Hey, Shige! You got some time today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.56,0:02:54.07,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Shige, did you do the homework?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.07,0:02:56.03,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shige! Let's go eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.03,0:02:58.61,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, Shige's funny as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:03:00.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Let's go hang out at Shige's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.07,0:03:01.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&}But if a transfer student\N who doesn't know the situation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:01.82,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Shige\NBut if a transfer student who\Ndoesn't know the situation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:04.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,comes and calls Shige "Matsuzaki"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.74,0:03:06.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,what do you think will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.50,0:03:09.37,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The whole school will be thrown into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:11.71,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Makes my hairs stand on end just imagining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.71,0:03:14.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, being thrown into chaos\Nis an exaggeration,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:16.67,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but it'll certainly spoil the mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.67,0:03:20.05,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In short, if you insist on giving us\Nyour real name no matter what,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:22.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,it'll spoil the mood for the whole school,\Nand {\i1}you{\i0} will be no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.51,0:03:27.47,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Then where can I vent this anger and sadness?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.47,0:03:29.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't be discouraged. I'll tell you a good story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:30.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:32.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's about an acquaintance\Nof mine from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.73,0:03:36.52,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He was called "Mr. Masao" and\Nhe was respected by everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.69,0:03:35.94,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\blur0.5\shad0\bord0\fnAnna\b0\c&H313137&\frz293.161\move(-19.259,183,242.443,183,0,2210)}Mr. Masao
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.94,0:03:39.74,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\blur0.5\shad0\bord0\fnAnna\b0\c&H313137&\frz293.161\fad(0,500)\pos(245.275,183)}Mr. Masao
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:37.57,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mr. Masao!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:38.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Mr. Masao!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.99,0:03:39.49,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:45.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\fad(400,350)\fs20\blur0.5\shad0\bord0\fnAnna\pos(531.335,72)\c&H315547&}Mr. Masao working
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.03,0:03:42.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mr. Masao's occupation was a carpenter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.78,0:03:44.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But it definitely wasn't\Nsomething he was good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:48.08,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Still, though, everyone in town liked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:49.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mr. Masao!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.20,0:03:50.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.04,0:03:51.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mr. Masao!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:53.37,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I was still a kid at the time\N and used to admire him too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.71,0:03:55.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, I kinda understand what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.88,0:03:58.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It seems a guy who's called by his\Nfirst name, rather than his last,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.63,0:04:01.01,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,is a popular guy who's respected\Nby everyone, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.38,0:04:05.01,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I guess it had been about three years\Nsince I had come to know Mr. Masao...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.01,0:04:07.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I went to see a dentist with Mr. Masao.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:13.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mr. Masao and I were waiting\N to be called in the waiting room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:17.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But the next moment\NI heard astonishing words!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.19,0:04:20.65,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kenji Masao, please come in\Nto the consultation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:21.49,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.49,0:04:21.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.99,0:04:22.86,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Kenji Masao?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:26.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Right... Masao wasn't his first name.\NIt was his last name!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:28.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mecha-ratta mecha-ratta mecha-ratta mecha-ratta.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:31.50,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:34.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mr. Masao was someone who just\Nnormally went by his last name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.79,0:04:36.00,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.00,0:04:39.13,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For a second, I felt like I was betrayed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.42,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I hadn't noticed it for three long years, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.88,0:04:44.22,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But when I think it over,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.22,0:04:47.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,it doesn't matter if Mr. Masao is\Nhis last name or his first name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:50.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,To me, Mr. Masao is Mr. Masao.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.35,0:04:55.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In short, I wanna tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.19,0:04:56.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,that's just the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.15,0:04:57.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.19,0:05:00.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I don't have a clue what he's trying to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.27,0:05:01.69,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\fs52\b0\shad0\bord1\blur0.3\c&H429ABE&\fnArnold 2.1\3c&H303D43&\frx0\fry356\frz2.91\pos(471.291,447)}The Ballad of{\c&HA55DAA&} Ishii{\c&H429ABE&}\N{\alphaff}aa{\alpha00} and{\c&H5BC25D&} Gotou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.15,0:05:03.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm still not convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.53,0:05:04.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.78,0:05:07.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh! Could it be about that\N names story from the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:09.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How dare you all join in and neglect my name!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.91,0:05:11.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Who the hell is Mr. Masao?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.41,0:05:12.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, listen carefully! My name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:14.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Like I said, hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:16.42,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Why do I have to hold on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:18.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There's a guy whose name is\NIshii in Class 3, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.63,0:05:20.29,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Do you know his real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.29,0:05:22.46,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?! Ishii's real name... isn't Ishii?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.46,0:05:25.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Actually, the real name of\NIshii in Class 3 is "Gotou."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.38,0:05:28.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's news to me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:29.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.14,0:05:30.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.81,0:05:33.18,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But why is Gotou called Ishii?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.18,0:05:34.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I don't know the details, either,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:38.65,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but I heard that the real name Gotou at\NClass 3 resembles Ishii in Class 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.65,0:05:40.31,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,and that's why he's called "Ishii."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.57,0:05:41.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What? Hold on a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:43.36,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\an7\fs26\shad0\c&H4264CD&\fnHumana Sans Md ITC TT\3c&H192C72&\bord0.8\pos(492.816,2)}Ishii{\fnAveria Sans\c&H242424&\bord0} In Class 3\N{\c&H888888&\bord0\b0\fs22}(real name:\N{\alphaff}aa{\alpha00} Gotou)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:43.36,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\an7\fs26\shad0\c&H4264CD&\fnHumana Sans Md ITC TT\3c&H192C72&\bord0.8\pos(492.816,250)}Ishii{\fnAveria Sans\c&H242424&\bord0} In Class 5
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.98,0:05:43.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Gotou and Ishii...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.48,0:05:45.49,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Those two don't look alike at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:47.07,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, I heard they act alike...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.07,0:05:49.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Even though people say they're alike...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:52.33,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Gotou has to be called Ishii because of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.33,0:05:53.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Isn't that how nicknames work?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:56.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, I have one question.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.66,0:05:58.96,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Is Ishii in Class 5 called "Gotou?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No, Ishii in Class 5 is "Ishii."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:02.13,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Isn't that unfair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:03.05,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.05,0:06:04.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So anyway, that's just the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:06.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He up and ended the discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.76,0:06:08.59,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:09.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:12.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I still don't have a clue what he's trying to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.27,0:06:16.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You're saying you wanna leave my corps?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:20.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yes. I have some thoughts of my own,\N so I decided to leave the Hokuto Corps...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.65,0:06:22.61,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see... That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.61,0:06:26.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,"Those who come are welcome, those who leave are not regretted." Do what you wanna do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.24,0:06:28.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You're not stopping him, Hokuto?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:31.62,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Since he says he wants to\Nleave, there's nothing I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.62,0:06:33.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see. I misjudged you, Hokuto!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:34.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.54,0:06:37.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I thought you were someone who had\Na warm heart though you looked cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:38.83,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Kamiyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.83,0:06:41.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't blame Mr. Hokuto!\NIt's me who's at fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.46,0:06:43.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What an immature thing to say... Nonsense...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:44.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm going home!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.38,0:06:46.34,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Wait, Hokuto! You shouldn't go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:51.30,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Can you go home and leave behind the one with whom you shared joys and sorrows up until now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.01,0:06:56.31,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hokuto, wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.14,0:06:57.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&}Get a move on! Come quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.02,0:07:03.90,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(350,500)\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\fs18\frz41.767\pos(498.481,258)\blur0.5\c&H474B6F&}Hokuto
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:06:58.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Here, look, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.81,0:07:00.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I made a uniform for the Hokuto Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.73,0:07:01.77,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You're a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.77,0:07:03.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's too embarrassing to\Nwear something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:06.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm drowning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.36,0:07:07.07,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&}Hold on! I'll save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:11.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Cry! Sob... Sob... Sob...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:11.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&}You fool. I told you not to swim in that river.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:12.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Sneeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:17.08,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, I remembered\Nour elementary school days...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.16,0:07:22.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There was that time you almost drowned in the\Nriver and I became frantic and saved you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.58,0:07:24.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hokuto...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.92,0:07:25.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:28.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We didn't come to know each other\Nuntil middle school...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.51,0:07:31.18,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh. That was Shimano...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:32.26,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:34.35,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.35,0:07:36.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I heard that guys from Bass High\Nabducted one of our students!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.51,0:07:37.35,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:38.77,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.77,0:07:39.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What is it, Yocchan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:42.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Why don't we send THOSE guys\Nonce in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:45.44,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We can't just let powerful guys\Nlike them go to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.44,0:07:47.11,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they attract lots of attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.11,0:07:48.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but they don't actually do anything useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.78,0:07:49.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,They sure don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.74,0:07:50.82,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.82,0:07:51.36,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.36,0:07:54.32,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Like I said, you go and tell them "go fight."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.32,0:07:57.08,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?! I don't know how to say it,\Nbut they look scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.08,0:07:59.83,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's not because they look strong,\Nbut they just look scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:02.71,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Geez, isn't there anyone who knows them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.08,0:08:04.96,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah! Let's ask Kamiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.96,0:08:06.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You called?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.09,0:08:08.46,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We want you to ask them to help us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.46,0:08:10.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hm. I'll at least ask them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.05,0:08:12.59,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:15.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, it's easier to communicate by drawing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.55,0:08:17.10,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Freddie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:22.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He says okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:23.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:26.86,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Now I tell you again: fighting\Nis not your purpose, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:29.32,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Ultimately your purpose is to\Nrescue our classmate, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.98,0:08:31.90,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Just in case, I'll at least draw a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.90,0:08:33.57,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:38.83,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's the wrong way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.83,0:08:40.49,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I still have a bad feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:42.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Freddie, you got the wrong people!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.33,0:08:45.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Those are Yakuza people, Freddie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:46.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,This isn't good. Stop him quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:48.67,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I explained this to you, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.67,0:08:50.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Your enemies are wearing school uniforms!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:52.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He squatted in defiance...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.92,0:08:54.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You think maybe that he's sulking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.68,0:08:57.30,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I guess we don't have a choice\Nbut to lead him to the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.26,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Be sure to follow me, okay, Freddie?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:01.72,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Just like a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:04.19,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(360.266,86)\be2}1 hour later
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:04.19,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fs26\shad0\c&H447F9B\bord2\be2\3c&H304C68&\frz345.146\frx340\fry330\org(576,304)\pos(561.924,331)}Bass\NHigh\NSchool
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.93,0:09:04.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We finally made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.48,0:09:07.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, the fools from Cromartie are finally here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.27,0:09:09.77,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We have a strong backer today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.15,0:09:12.65,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You mean that old guy there is your backer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:16.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, he probably looks just like some\Nregular old guy to small fry like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but he's different from ordinary\Nold guys you can find anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.78,0:09:20.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,This guy is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.24,0:09:22.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, he IS an ordinary old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.91,0:09:24.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Who is this old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.21,0:09:26.37,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh? Where did I make a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:30.84,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And so... Freddie wasn't useful at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.21,0:09:34.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We should have asked this guy after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:36.97,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought,\N but let's not ask Gorilla after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:37.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.51,0:09:41.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How did this man stray in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:44.39,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It seems he switched places\Nwith Mr. Imai somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.39,0:09:46.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I don't understand what you mean at all! Where's Imai?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.31,0:09:48.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.27,0:09:52.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The president of Sipin Trading Company says he\Nwon't talk to anyone but the man in charge, Imai.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.19,0:09:54.36,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So if Imai isn't here, we're not\Ngoing to get anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.36,0:09:55.61,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.61,0:09:57.36,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He's already waiting in the other room!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:10:00.83,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If it's hopeless anyway, let's try staking our company's future on this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.83,0:10:02.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Entrust our company's future with {\i1}him{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:03.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,As a first step, I'll put a tie on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.99,0:10:05.16,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358,287)\shad0\bord0\fnArial\c&H1B1220&\blur0.4\fs34}Conference Room
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.99,0:10:07.96,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So, we took a great deal of damage this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.96,0:10:10.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Do you have any explanation for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.05,0:10:15.42,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You didn't think up even one\Nexcuse before coming here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:19.72,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Are you going to just stay silent like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.09,0:10:21.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, no... Just as I thought, it's not working...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:23.39,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Good! I like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.68,0:10:27.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Lots of people give stupid excuses\Nthese days when they make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:30.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,To be honest, I was getting fed up with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:32.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Admitting his own fault\Nwithout making excuses...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.27,0:10:34.90,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen an honest man\Nlike him in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:37.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I think we can work with someone like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.61,0:10:39.57,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Does that mean that\N the contract will stay like it has been?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.57,0:10:44.99,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\an8\c&H21212D&\shad0\fnBrushed\3c&H7A8EA7&\bord3\pos(396.519,5)}Great\N Ambition
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.11,0:10:41.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But this man isn't Imai, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.12,0:10:43.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you figured it out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.95,0:10:44.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't stamp it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.96,0:11:44.97,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\alpha130\fs24\fnNeon\bord0\c&H4E1728&\blur0.5\pos(346.671,139)}Next\N\N\N\NEpisode
Dialogue: 1,0:11:44.97,0:11:49.98,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fs26\blur0.5\fnArial Black\bord3\c&H000000&\3c&HFBFAFC&\pos(192.595,50)}Sakigake!!\NCromartie High School
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.97,0:11:49.98,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fs26\blur0.6\fnArial Black\bord3.2\c&H000000&\3c&H3F3F3F&\pos(192.595,50)}Sakigake!!\NCromartie High School
